---
import Page from "@/layouts/Page.astro";
import Carousel from "@/components/Carousel.tsx";
import FAQAccordion from "@/components/FAQAccordion.tsx";
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Trophy } from "lucide-react";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
// Aseg√∫rate de tener esta imagen en tu carpeta assets
import culpeoImage from "../../assets/culpeo.jpg"; 
---

<Page title="About">
  <div class="relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute -z-10 top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 opacity-5 pointer-events-none">
      <Trophy size={600} color="#dddddd" strokeWidth={1} />
    </div>

    <div class="container mx-auto py-8 space-y-16">
      
      <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-8">2026 ICPC Latin America Championship</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          The International Collegiate Programming Contest is the oldest, largest and
          most prestigious programming contest for university students. In teams of
          three, students represent their institutions, practicing their algorithmic
          skills, teamwork, creativity and the ability to perform under pressure.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
          Since the first championship in 1977, the ICPC has evolved into a global
          competition, with universities around the world hosting regional rounds that
          qualify teams for the World Finals. For this purpose, the Latin America
          Championship brings together the best Latin American teams.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-t border-border/40" />

      <section>
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Meet our Mascot</h2>
          <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground">
            The official mascot of ICPC Latin America 2026: <span class="text-logo-orange font-bold">The Culpeo Fox</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-12 bg-card border rounded-3xl p-6 md:p-10 shadow-sm">
          
          <div class="w-full lg:w-1/2">
            <div class="relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-lg transition-transform duration-500">
              <Image 
                src={culpeoImage} 
                alt="Culpeo Fox - ICPC Mascot" 
                class="w-full h-[400px] object-cover"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 space-y-6">
            <div>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                The Culpeo Fox perfectly embodies the spirit of those who participate in ICPC. It is an intelligent, curious, and adaptable animal, capable of moving with agility in challenging environments and solving problems with cunning, much like what teams experience during the competition.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
                This fox is one of Chile's most representative animals, found throughout much of the country. The culpeo fox is found in almost all of Chile, from sea level to an altitude of 4,500 meters, adapting to a wide variety of environments such as the coast, the desert, the Andes mountains, forests, and the steppe, ranging from Arica to Magallanes and Tierra del Fuego, and is the largest fox in the country. Although it also lives in other parts of Latin America, its strong presence in Chile makes it the perfect symbol for thisedition of the competition held in Santiago. Thus, our mascot connects the host country's identity with the talent, diversity, and Latin American spirit that define ICPC.
              </p>
            </div>


          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Page>